1
00:00:26,635 --> 00:00:29,159
[vocalizing]

2
00:00:34,208 --> 00:00:36,601
[distant vocalizing]

3
00:00:36,645 --> 00:00:39,169
[choir singing]

4
00:01:10,635 --> 00:01:13,160
[bright music]

5
00:01:52,851 --> 00:01:55,376
[choir singing]

6
00:03:01,572 --> 00:03:04,140
[cricket chirring]

7
00:03:35,867 --> 00:03:37,304
We're movin'.

8
00:03:38,914 --> 00:03:40,220
What?

9
00:03:44,006 --> 00:03:45,442
We're movin'.

10
00:03:49,229 --> 00:03:50,882
We're gonna move.

11
00:03:53,363 --> 00:03:55,757
When?

12
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:58,629
Two days.

13
00:03:58,673 --> 00:04:00,762
In two days?

14
00:04:00,805 --> 00:04:02,329
Yeah.

15
00:04:07,725 --> 00:04:09,379
Not really.

16
00:04:20,869 --> 00:04:22,131
Thanks for the news.

17
00:04:27,484 --> 00:04:29,269
I haven't known for long.

18
00:04:34,491 --> 00:04:38,843
I just decided,
I decided on Butte.

19
00:04:38,887 --> 00:04:41,063
Butte, Montana.

20
00:04:48,462 --> 00:04:51,900
What do I need that makes me
make these decisions?

21
00:04:55,817 --> 00:04:57,427
You got me.

22
00:05:02,954 --> 00:05:06,218
-Yeah.
What does Beth say?

23
00:05:07,568 --> 00:05:10,005
Beth?

24
00:05:10,048 --> 00:05:12,834
She says...

25
00:05:12,877 --> 00:05:17,839
Beth says whatever makes me
happy, that's what she says.

26
00:05:17,882 --> 00:05:20,407
[engine idling]

27
00:05:23,192 --> 00:05:26,021
[car radio]

28
00:05:26,064 --> 00:05:28,589
[horns beeping]

29
00:05:36,423 --> 00:05:38,990
[beeps horn]

30
00:06:02,971 --> 00:06:05,495
[rhythmic clicking]

31
00:06:07,889 --> 00:06:10,413
How long a drive is it to Butte?

32
00:06:10,457 --> 00:06:12,546
With me driving?

33
00:06:12,589 --> 00:06:15,026
Twenty-two hours.

34
00:06:15,070 --> 00:06:16,854
That's not bad.

35
00:06:16,898 --> 00:06:21,642
In my car? It's a fuckin'
nightmare.

36
00:06:21,685 --> 00:06:24,340
And there's no good radio in
Utah.

37
00:06:24,384 --> 00:06:29,954
-It's all religious programs.
-Get saved.

38
00:06:29,998 --> 00:06:32,130
No thank you.

39
00:06:32,174 --> 00:06:33,915
[giggling]

40
00:06:33,958 --> 00:06:35,873
Uh-uh.

41
00:06:37,919 --> 00:06:41,052
Think about this.

42
00:06:41,096 --> 00:06:43,185
Take a detour

43
00:06:43,228 --> 00:06:47,232
and go through Vegas.

44
00:06:47,276 --> 00:06:48,843
Kick off the trip.

45
00:06:48,886 --> 00:06:50,888
You and Beth can have
a nice, romantic dinner,

46
00:06:50,932 --> 00:06:53,935
see a show, play the slots,

47
00:06:53,978 --> 00:06:56,894
get the free drinks.

48
00:06:56,938 --> 00:06:58,505
No, that's too much money.

49
00:07:01,159 --> 00:07:03,379
The show, the meal, the slots.

50
00:07:03,423 --> 00:07:06,991
Then there's the hotel.

51
00:07:07,035 --> 00:07:09,385
That's another hundred
down the toilet.

52
00:07:09,429 --> 00:07:10,908
No!

53
00:07:10,952 --> 00:07:13,737
You skip the hotel--it's night.

54
00:07:13,781 --> 00:07:15,304
The highway's empty.

55
00:07:15,347 --> 00:07:16,740
[laughs]

56
00:07:16,784 --> 00:07:20,135
You, uh, you start speeding.

57
00:07:20,178 --> 00:07:21,832
'Cause you've got
a little buzz on.

58
00:07:21,876 --> 00:07:24,356
You get stopped in Utah
by the cops.

59
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:26,141
You flunk the breathalyzer.

60
00:07:26,184 --> 00:07:27,490
They haul you in.

61
00:07:27,534 --> 00:07:29,144
The judge is Mormon.

62
00:07:29,187 --> 00:07:32,060
Ugh! You get 15 years.

63
00:07:32,103 --> 00:07:33,540
You go to prison,

64
00:07:33,583 --> 00:07:36,804
but at least your life
has taken a direction!

65
00:07:36,847 --> 00:07:38,066
[shrieks]

66
00:07:38,109 --> 00:07:40,634
[laughter]

67
00:07:47,554 --> 00:07:48,946
Hi.

68
00:07:50,078 --> 00:07:51,906
Hi!

69
00:07:57,085 --> 00:07:58,565
Hi, honey.

70
00:07:59,957 --> 00:08:01,481
Hi, honey.

71
00:08:03,091 --> 00:08:05,963
-Bye.
-Bye!

72
00:08:06,007 --> 00:08:07,661
Lunch tomorrow?

73
00:08:07,704 --> 00:08:09,184
I'm all yours.

74
00:08:09,227 --> 00:08:11,926
Wait--make it mine,
I've got the short shift.

75
00:08:15,886 --> 00:08:17,540
Do you want me to come over
after?

76
00:08:19,411 --> 00:08:21,805
Help pack?

77
00:08:21,849 --> 00:08:24,155
Yeah, that'd be great.

78
00:08:24,199 --> 00:08:26,941
I'm--I'm really--
I'm really sorry

79
00:08:26,984 --> 00:08:29,465
we didn't tell you any sooner,
it's...

80
00:08:29,509 --> 00:08:31,728
he just...

81
00:08:31,772 --> 00:08:34,949
Yeah, oh, I understand.

82
00:08:39,954 --> 00:08:41,303
Bye.

83
00:08:52,009 --> 00:08:53,707
Fuckin' Nick.

84
00:08:59,626 --> 00:09:03,151
I'm tired,
I'm going to bed.

85
00:09:03,194 --> 00:09:04,979
What's your problem?

86
00:09:05,022 --> 00:09:08,504
I haven't got a problem.

87
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:10,071
Okay.

88
00:09:14,031 --> 00:09:16,338
You agreed to try Butte.

89
00:09:16,381 --> 00:09:19,646
Yeah, I know--Butte, Montana,
city of the future.

90
00:09:19,689 --> 00:09:21,038
Yeah, I read that a while ago,

91
00:09:21,082 --> 00:09:23,824
so the future's probably
already there.

92
00:09:26,783 --> 00:09:28,785
It's not like you're leaving
anything behind,

93
00:09:28,829 --> 00:09:30,482
a good job or something.

94
00:09:30,526 --> 00:09:33,007
No, just some friends.

95
00:09:33,050 --> 00:09:34,922
You'll make new friends.

96
00:09:34,965 --> 00:09:36,401
I know.

97
00:09:36,445 --> 00:09:40,536
I'm not eight years old,
I know I'll make new friends.

98
00:09:40,580 --> 00:09:42,146
So what is it?

99
00:09:45,802 --> 00:09:47,761
Uh...

100
00:09:47,804 --> 00:09:49,414
it embarrasses me.

101
00:09:49,458 --> 00:09:54,724
I mean, the way that you and
Carol are together sometimes.

102
00:09:54,768 --> 00:09:56,204
She's my best friend

103
00:09:56,247 --> 00:10:00,948
and it embarrasses methat you used to live with her.

104
00:10:00,991 --> 00:10:02,340
That was years ago.

105
00:10:02,384 --> 00:10:03,951
It was three years.

106
00:10:03,994 --> 00:10:05,605
Yeah.

107
00:10:09,957 --> 00:10:12,002
We're moving, so...

108
00:10:12,046 --> 00:10:14,614
she won't be your best friend
anymore.

109
00:10:29,498 --> 00:10:32,457
Livin' with someone
isn't such a big deal.

110
00:10:35,025 --> 00:10:37,158
Anyway, I live with you now.

111
00:10:38,463 --> 00:10:40,988
[choir singing]

112
00:11:12,236 --> 00:11:15,065
[coffee machine gurgles]

113
00:11:15,109 --> 00:11:17,328
Beth?

114
00:11:17,372 --> 00:11:20,331
Beth!

115
00:11:20,375 --> 00:11:22,203
Beth?

116
00:11:22,246 --> 00:11:24,161
What?

117
00:11:30,777 --> 00:11:32,039
It's rainin'.

118
00:11:32,082 --> 00:11:34,302
It does that.

119
00:11:34,345 --> 00:11:35,303
Since we got it?

120
00:11:35,346 --> 00:11:37,827
No, lately.

121
00:11:37,871 --> 00:11:39,916
Shit. What's wrong with it?

122
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:41,657
Water comes out.

123
00:11:41,701 --> 00:11:43,572
Shit. I hate this shit.

124
00:11:43,615 --> 00:11:45,922
Never kept the coffee hot,
and now this.

125
00:11:45,966 --> 00:11:47,794
It still works.

126
00:11:47,837 --> 00:11:49,186
No it doesn't.

127
00:11:49,230 --> 00:11:51,406
Water comes out.

128
00:11:51,449 --> 00:11:52,973
Okay.

129
00:11:53,016 --> 00:11:56,324
Coulda got a new one on mydiscount but it's too late now.

130
00:11:56,367 --> 00:11:59,675
-Want a doughnut?
-No.

131
00:11:59,719 --> 00:12:04,462
I want an appliance that works.

132
00:12:04,506 --> 00:12:08,162
This coffeemaker is junk.

133
00:12:13,123 --> 00:12:14,429
[blender buzzing]

134
00:12:16,344 --> 00:12:18,302
Blender is junk!

135
00:12:24,221 --> 00:12:26,093
Our TV is junk.

136
00:12:26,136 --> 00:12:28,748
I don't know why
we're even bothering to pack.

137
00:12:28,791 --> 00:12:31,185
You got me.

138
00:12:31,228 --> 00:12:33,927
Can't believe we don't have
a good TV.

139
00:12:33,970 --> 00:12:35,929
Well, we don't watch much.

140
00:12:35,972 --> 00:12:39,323
Yeah, but at our age...

141
00:12:39,367 --> 00:12:41,543
Why don't you take one?

142
00:12:41,586 --> 00:12:43,980
Ain't hungry.

143
00:12:44,024 --> 00:12:46,243
Not a doughnut--a TV.

144
00:12:49,594 --> 00:12:50,944
I might do it.

145
00:12:50,987 --> 00:12:52,684
I say do it.

146
00:12:52,728 --> 00:12:55,470
They can afford
to give you a bonus.

147
00:12:55,513 --> 00:12:57,341
Maybe they are.

148
00:12:57,385 --> 00:12:58,429
What do you mean?

149
00:12:58,473 --> 00:13:00,823
Maybe when I get my check today,

150
00:13:00,867 --> 00:13:03,391
there'll be a bonus in it.

151
00:13:03,434 --> 00:13:06,133
Nick, they fired you.

152
00:13:06,176 --> 00:13:07,612
Yeah.

153
00:13:07,656 --> 00:13:10,441
There's no bonus.

154
00:13:10,485 --> 00:13:12,400
Yeah.

155
00:13:12,443 --> 00:13:16,186
And I sold a lot of TVs for 'em.

156
00:13:16,230 --> 00:13:17,622
I should go.

157
00:13:17,666 --> 00:13:19,450
Don't wanna be late
on my last day.

158
00:13:30,026 --> 00:13:31,245
Gotta go.

159
00:13:38,687 --> 00:13:39,949
[engine fires up]

160
00:13:55,312 --> 00:13:57,837
[tires screeching]

161
00:14:05,583 --> 00:14:06,846
[tires screech]

162
00:14:16,377 --> 00:14:18,901
Hot enough for you?

163
00:14:18,945 --> 00:14:20,511
Hey, Chip.

164
00:14:20,555 --> 00:14:22,383
Supposed to hit 110.

165
00:14:22,426 --> 00:14:26,561
Yeah, well, it's good practice
for hell.

166
00:14:26,604 --> 00:14:28,737
I'll remember that one.

167
00:14:28,780 --> 00:14:32,349
Hey, um, I heard that you're
leaving us.

168
00:14:32,393 --> 00:14:34,438
Yep. I'm outta here.

169
00:14:34,482 --> 00:14:36,397
They can you?

170
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:38,529
That's what they think.

171
00:14:38,573 --> 00:14:40,314
Yeah?

172
00:14:40,357 --> 00:14:42,882
Yeah, I was gonna quit anyway.

173
00:14:42,925 --> 00:14:44,535
This way, I get unemployment.

174
00:14:44,579 --> 00:14:48,539
I'm not stuck waiting around
for the layoffs to start.

175
00:14:48,583 --> 00:14:49,671
Layoffs?

176
00:14:49,714 --> 00:14:50,977
[elevator dings]

177
00:15:13,173 --> 00:15:15,740
[door opens, closes]

178
00:15:22,182 --> 00:15:24,532
-Who are you?
-The painter.

179
00:15:24,575 --> 00:15:26,316
What are you doing?

180
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:27,839
Painting.

181
00:15:32,279 --> 00:15:34,063
Well!

182
00:15:34,107 --> 00:15:35,717
Good morning!

183
00:15:35,760 --> 00:15:37,284
You.

184
00:15:37,327 --> 00:15:40,591
Sid. Nice to see you again.

185
00:15:40,635 --> 00:15:43,420
-Why are you here?
-To paint.

186
00:15:43,464 --> 00:15:46,641
Realty office likes a fresh coatbetween tenants.

187
00:15:46,684 --> 00:15:49,600
But we're still here.

188
00:15:49,644 --> 00:15:52,299
Well, they said you'd be gone.

189
00:15:52,342 --> 00:15:53,648
We're not.

190
00:15:56,042 --> 00:15:59,654
I've done this house before.

191
00:15:59,697 --> 00:16:01,786
Did a pretty good job.

192
00:16:01,830 --> 00:16:05,355
Won't have to redo the trim.

193
00:16:05,399 --> 00:16:08,576
Oh, fuck--could you come back
tomorrow?

194
00:16:08,619 --> 00:16:11,100
Tomorrow's Sunday.

195
00:16:11,144 --> 00:16:12,797
Yeah?

196
00:16:12,841 --> 00:16:14,538
New tenants move in on Sunday.

197
00:16:17,150 --> 00:16:18,934
Where you movin' to?

198
00:16:18,978 --> 00:16:22,285
Um, Butte, Montana.

199
00:16:22,329 --> 00:16:25,549
Why?

200
00:16:25,593 --> 00:16:29,553
Can't be any worse than Enfield,Arizona.

201
00:16:29,597 --> 00:16:32,687
I've lived in Enfield my whole
life.

202
00:16:32,730 --> 00:16:35,037
You hold this?

203
00:16:35,081 --> 00:16:37,257
It's masking tape.

204
00:16:37,300 --> 00:16:39,433
I use it to mask.

205
00:16:39,476 --> 00:16:42,305
Do you ever use masking tape tomask?

206
00:16:42,349 --> 00:16:43,741
No, I haven't.

207
00:16:43,785 --> 00:16:45,047
[tape snaps]

208
00:17:04,936 --> 00:17:06,329
Sorry I'm late.

209
00:17:06,373 --> 00:17:07,809
The new girl is a moron.

210
00:17:07,852 --> 00:17:09,115
What's that?

211
00:17:10,725 --> 00:17:13,249
A going-away present.

212
00:17:13,293 --> 00:17:14,598
Thanks!

213
00:17:24,739 --> 00:17:25,827
A map.

214
00:17:25,870 --> 00:17:27,263
I thought you might need it.

215
00:17:27,307 --> 00:17:28,656
I do.

216
00:17:28,699 --> 00:17:30,571
I had a map, I lost it.

217
00:17:33,269 --> 00:17:34,966
Let's highlight your route.

218
00:17:40,798 --> 00:17:42,713
Okay.

219
00:17:42,757 --> 00:17:44,150
Here's Enfield.

220
00:17:48,632 --> 00:17:50,678
Here's Butte.

221
00:17:50,721 --> 00:17:53,463
Where?

222
00:17:53,507 --> 00:17:54,595
Right there.

223
00:17:54,638 --> 00:17:55,987
Okay.

224
00:17:58,207 --> 00:18:00,775
[humming]

225
00:18:03,604 --> 00:18:05,562
-Look at that.
-What?

226
00:18:05,606 --> 00:18:06,563
-Right there?
-Uh-huh.

227
00:18:06,607 --> 00:18:08,609
Halfway?

228
00:18:08,652 --> 00:18:11,829
That's the town I was born in.

229
00:18:11,873 --> 00:18:16,051
Where I grew up,
where my parents live.

230
00:18:16,095 --> 00:18:17,835
Isn't that a coincidence.

231
00:18:20,882 --> 00:18:22,840
Visit 'em.

232
00:18:22,884 --> 00:18:24,146
Nope.

233
00:18:25,974 --> 00:18:29,020
You're gonna be driving by.

234
00:18:29,064 --> 00:18:30,848
Nope.

235
00:18:30,892 --> 00:18:33,764
They're not near the interstate.

236
00:18:33,808 --> 00:18:36,376
I haven't even called them in
years.

237
00:18:36,419 --> 00:18:37,986
You might as well visit.

238
00:18:38,029 --> 00:18:39,640
Nope.

239
00:18:39,683 --> 00:18:40,858
Why not?

240
00:18:40,902 --> 00:18:42,512
Wouldn't know 'em.

241
00:18:47,256 --> 00:18:48,910
Wait, let me.

242
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:02,619
Pretty good.

243
00:19:06,667 --> 00:19:08,147
I'm starving.

244
00:19:10,758 --> 00:19:13,543
-Oops.
-Hello?

245
00:19:13,587 --> 00:19:16,155
[mellow music]

246
00:19:44,574 --> 00:19:45,967
I'm lucky I don't have to kill
'em.

247
00:19:46,010 --> 00:19:47,795
What?

248
00:19:47,838 --> 00:19:49,710
If these walls were any darker,

249
00:19:49,753 --> 00:19:51,929
I'd have to put a layer of killdown first

250
00:19:51,973 --> 00:19:56,151
so that the old paint
wouldn't bleed through.

251
00:19:56,195 --> 00:19:58,545
Oh.

252
00:19:58,588 --> 00:19:59,894
Yep.

253
00:20:01,765 --> 00:20:06,422
Kill is an alcohol-based paint.

254
00:20:06,466 --> 00:20:07,815
Covers the old paint

255
00:20:07,858 --> 00:20:09,817
so that you'd never know
it was there, but--

256
00:20:09,860 --> 00:20:13,821
but when it's drying,
it gives off these fumes.

257
00:20:13,864 --> 00:20:16,215
The fumes are noxious.

258
00:20:16,258 --> 00:20:18,042
Noxious fumes.

259
00:20:18,086 --> 00:20:22,351
They, uh, they'd probably
find us on the floor,

260
00:20:22,395 --> 00:20:23,961
unconscious.

261
00:20:24,005 --> 00:20:25,311
"They"?

262
00:20:25,354 --> 00:20:28,531
Yeah, the "they" that find
people unconscious.

263
00:20:28,575 --> 00:20:31,055
-Nick.
-Nick.

264
00:20:31,099 --> 00:20:34,407
Nick, the man I live with.

265
00:20:34,450 --> 00:20:36,800
I guess he'd be the "they."

266
00:20:36,844 --> 00:20:38,846
Yes.

267
00:20:38,889 --> 00:20:40,108
He'd find us,

268
00:20:40,151 --> 00:20:42,458
and he'd be surprised.

269
00:20:49,378 --> 00:20:50,684
It was the drive
that killed us.

270
00:20:50,727 --> 00:20:52,163
Ugh.

271
00:20:52,207 --> 00:20:56,037
San Antonio to Seattleis just too many hours in a car.

272
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:59,040
-If we'da flown, we'da made it.
-No!

273
00:20:59,083 --> 00:21:01,390
Things were all right in bed.

274
00:21:01,434 --> 00:21:04,872
Yeah, but the rest of the time,they were awful.

275
00:21:04,915 --> 00:21:06,743
-Really?
-Yeah! Nick,

276
00:21:06,787 --> 00:21:08,832
we couldn't stand each other.

277
00:21:08,876 --> 00:21:12,401
When we got to Enfield,
I dumped you, and, uh,

278
00:21:12,445 --> 00:21:14,838
we just stayed.

279
00:21:14,882 --> 00:21:19,060
Why didn't you go on to Seattle?It was your car.

280
00:21:19,103 --> 00:21:20,975
Big trees scare me.

281
00:21:23,673 --> 00:21:27,024
I'm thinkin' about stealin'
a TV.

